OL,3,CFire expert critical of Summerland but
OL,4,Cdoes not see it as 'an injustice'
OL,6,FThe outer wall material had been
OL,7,Fchanged from concrete, to a metal
OL,8,Fcladding called galbestos, a material
OL,9,Fthat was used to save money, but was
OL,10,Falso highly flammable.
OL,12,F"It surprised all of us, particularly
OL,13,Fthe chief fire officer", John explains.
OL,15,F"That's when we realised that
OL,16,Fparticular alteration wasn't referred
OL,17,Fback to him or the fire service and it
OL,18,Fshould have been".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
