OL,3,CFire expert critical of Summerland but
OL,4,Cdoes not see it as 'an injustice'
OL,6,FHe said: "If it had been better run,
OL,7,Fit was a reasonably safe building had
OL,8,Fstaff been trained better".
OL,10,FHe recalled the report noted "there
OL,11,Fwere no villains", something he
OL,12,Fbelieved was right, adding "it was
OL,13,Fmore ignorance than villainy, it
OL,14,Fwasn't deliberate".
OL,16,FA verdict of misadventure was given to
OL,17,Fthose who died, something campaigners
OL,18,Fwant changed.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
